  "text": "Acute phase proteins have not been evaluated in such detail in small ruminants as in cattle, but it appears that the acute phase response is similar. Despite the clinical value of the determination of acute phase proteins also in small ruminants, there is a lack of information about their use in ovine and caprine practice. In these species, Hp and SAA are considered the major acute phase proteins, with 80 and 22 fold increases in experimentally induced inflammatory conditions, respectively. Concentrations of AGP and fibrinogen in this experiment showed only 2-and 3.5-fold increases, while albumin values decreased significantly [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ).",
